data.chText: 难以达到的；不可得到的
data.enText: difficult or impossible to reach or to get

data.chText: 他们住在一处偏远地区，只能开车去。
data.enText: They live in a remote area, inaccessible except by car.

data.chText: 这个寺庙现在不对公众开放。
data.enText: The temple is now inaccessible to the public.

data.chText: 青少年的语言成人往往听不懂。
data.enText: The language of teenagers is often completely inaccessible to (= not understood by) adults.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 不，无，非 + accessible 可到达的 → 不可及的

tr: capable of being reached only with great difficulty or not at all

example: a rare work, today almost inaccessible
timber is virtually unobtainable in the islands
untouchable resources buried deep within the earth

value.def: An inaccessible place is very difficult or impossible to reach.

example.ex: ...the remote, inaccessible areas of the Andes rainforests.
example.tran: 偏僻遥远、难以到达的安第斯雨林地区

example.ex: The route took us through scenery quite inaccessible to the motorist.
example.tran: 这条路线带我们穿越了驾车者难以抵达的风景区。

value.tran: 达不到的;难到达的;不可(或不易)进入的

example.ex: Its inaccessibility makes food distribution difficult.
example.tran: 这里地处偏僻，食品发放十分困难。

value.def: If something is inaccessible, you are unable to see, use, or buy it.

example.ex: Ninety-five per cent of its magnificent collection will remain inaccessible to the public...
example.tran: 其中 95% 的顶级收藏品仍不会向公众开放。

example.ex: We gained a rich supply of data which would normally be inaccessible.
example.tran: 我们得到了通常难以获取的大量数据。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>to</l> n

value.tran: 见不到的;不可使用的;买不到的

example.ex: ...the problem of inaccessibility of essential goods.
example.tran: 必需品难以买到的问题

value.def: Someone or something that is inaccessible is difficult or impossible to understand or appreciate.

example.ex: A lot of contemporary music is virtually inaccessible.
example.tran: 许多当代音乐几乎难以理解。

example.ex: ...using language that is inaccessible to working people.
example.tran: 使用劳动人民无法理解的语言

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>to</l> n

example.tran: 他的文学作品艰深难懂
